This paper is about building a universal neural machine translation system, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various aspects of model building, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions transfer learning, which is a popular research area in artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which falls under the category of neural networks (NE), making cs.NE another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practicality of the proposed system, which involves image processing techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
